Before doing a mvn install, add the following to your settings.xml file:

1. Add a profile under <profiles> with id "1.5_compiler"

     <profile>
       <id>1.5_compiler</id>
       <activation>
         <jdk>1.5</jdk>
       </activation>
       <properties>
         <JAVA_1_5_HOME>/opt/binaries/jdk1.5.0_09</JAVA_1_5_HOME>
       </properties>
     </profile>

2. Add another profile called "1.6_compiler"

     <profile>
       <id>1.6_compiler</id>
       <activation>
         <jdk>1.6</jdk>
       </activation>
       <properties>
         <JAVA_1_6_HOME>/opt/binaries/jdk1.6.0_04</JAVA_1_6_HOME>
       </properties>
     </profile>

One of the above profiles are activated based on your system settings, so as to compile the sources
under jdbc30 and jdbc40 modules respectively.

